### THE GUIDE TO ONLINE LEARNING WITH SNA-LABS CLI VPN

Welcome to the journey of learning how to use the SNA-LABS CLI VPN with our labs. To effectively use the VPN, it's essential to understand how our labs work. Let's dive into it.



[![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/ninjaconnect/month)](https://pepy.tech/project/ninjaconnect)
[![Supported Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/rich/13.2.0)](https://pypi.org/project/rich/)
[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/ninjaconnect.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/ninjaconnect)
![ninjaconnect](https://img.shields.io/badge/ninjaconnector-blue)

### Steps to Connect with your Labs

### Supported Platforms

After joining our platform, you can connect to our labs with this VPN.

### Installation on Linux

![linux](https://img.shields.io/badge/Linux-FCC624?style=for-the-badge&logo=linux&logoColor=black)

On Linux, you can install NinjaConnect easily with pipx using the following command:

```bash
pipx install ninjaconnect
```
Some cases it will ask permissions we need to give permission
```
chmod +x /home/<yourusername>/.local/bin/ninja
```
After installation, you can run the command below the steps terminal:

### Installation on Windows
![windows](https://img.shields.io/badge/Windows-0078D6?style=for-the-badge&logo=windows&logoColor=white)
```
pipx install ninjaconnect
```
On Windows, you can install NinjaConnect with pip. After that, you need to create a batch file as shown in the image and replace <Your Username> with your actual username. Place this batch file in your user folder.

```batch
@echo off
python C:\Users\<Your Username>\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312\Scripts\ninja %*
```
To run this VPN, open the command prompt as an administrator on windows


### Raspberry Pi
```bash
pipx install ninjaconnect
```
For Raspberry pi you need to generate access token for 
Login authenticate ourlabs
[GENERATELINK](accesstoken.md)

![raspberrypi](https://img.shields.io/badge/Raspberrypi(Headlessdevices)-darkred?logo=raspberrypi
)

### Configure Your Device SSH
After installation, you need to configure SSH on your device to connect via SSH or with VS Code. For configuring SSH, refer to SSHCONF.

### Help and Options
Some cases it will ask permissions we need to give permission
```
chmod +x /home/<yourusername>/.local/bin/ninja
```
To see available options, use the following command:

```bash
ninja -h
```
![helpoption](https://i.imgur.com/gZHrKhM.png)

This command will show you what you can do with this tool.

#### Step 1: Configuration

```bash
ninja configure
```
![configure](https://i.imgur.com/8yHkjat.png)

`Note: In case any errors occur, reconfigure it.`

#### Step 2: Login

```bash
ninja login
```
![login](https://i.imgur.com/ghjSuaa.png)
Above the login for only GUI devices
For Headless devices you need to give access token
#### Step 3: Add Device
```bash
ninja add_device
```
![add_device](https://i.imgur.com/LstuXGA.png)

#### Step 4: Connect
```
ninja connect
```
![connect](https://i.imgur.com/ofoa59k.png)

Now you can connect via VSCODE and SSH into your labs' IP.

#### Step 5: Disconnect

```bash
ninja disconnect
```
![disconnect](https://i.imgur.com/BpEffjl.png)

#### Step 6: Logout

```bash
ninja logout
```
![logout](https://i.imgur.com/ceiUmCl.png)

#### Step 7: Remove Device
Incase if you want to remove the device you canable to remove the device with this command 
```bash
ninja remove_device
```
